narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor define the topic of study?
How clearly did the instructor outline the expectation for the course, classroom activity and homework?
How well were individual class sessions prepared and presented?
comments: Class sessions were always prepared and presented very well.

narratives.question_text: How well did lectures fit within the boundaries of the course?
comments: I was great when he had us close our books and we discussed the martial being taught.
It seemed like the right amount of homework. I was always able to get it done without feeling overwhelmed by it.

narratives.question_text: How available was the instructor for help outside the classroom?
comments: Excellent TA who was always ready and willing to help

I'm responding to the availability of our TA, who unfortunately being the TD of Carlotta was understandably not quite available near the end of the term. That being said, he tried really hard to make time where he could and answer my questions when I had them.

narratives.question_text: How useful were assignments in furthering an understanding of the topic?
If tests were given, how fairly did they measure knowledge gained?
How useful was this course in preparing you for production work?
comments: I think I understand production work better as a result of Structures.
While I wont use it often having the knowledge is incredibly beneficial.

narratives.question_text: How would you evaluate the instructor's knowledge of the material?
Please offer additional comments on such topics as: what worked best about the course, suggested improvements, class materials, etc.
comments: I really enjoyed the "off book" discussions and example problems we did together in class this semester. The example problems done in class were so helpful in my understanding. When we broke into two groups and solved for the lightest square and rectangular tube or HSS vs Mechanical tube made the equations feel like something I could use in the really world and not just a collection of problems.
It would be nice to have practice problems, that weren't necessarily marked but would allow us to go through problem after we got our homework back to try and do it the right way.
I think the discussions are great.
